meta {
  name: POST vehicle wakeup
  type: http
  seq: 14
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v1/vehicle-wakeup/{{vin}}?applyRequestLimiter=true
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {}
}

docs {
  Wakes the vehicle so subsequent polls return fresh data instead of
  the last-known cached snapshot. Empty JSON body. The
  ``applyRequestLimiter=true`` query parameter is REQUIRED — without
  it the backend rate-limits aggressively and may bounce wakeups for
  hours after a single use. With the limiter active mysmob enforces
  ~one wakeup per 5 minutes which is exactly what we want.

  Implementation: SkodaClient.command_wake() in
  custom_components/vag_connect/cariad/api/skoda.py:461.

  Backs the button.<vin>_wake_up entity. No S-PIN needed.
}
